## Critical Rules â€” Agents MUST Follow

### âś‹ Ticket Persistence Rules

- **NEVER** use `Write` or `Edit` tools on any file in `.flux/` or `.flux-store/` â€” these are engine-managed.
- **NEVER** use `Bash` to write to ticket files (no `echo`, `sed`, `cat >`, etc.).
- **ALWAYS** use the MCP tools below for ticket updates. They handle schema validation and history normalization.

**Why?** Direct file writes bypass engine validation and corrupt ticket history. Changes that only exist in chat are lost â€” the engine is the single source of truth.

### đź› ď¸Ź MCP Tools (Use These For All Ticket Work)

| Tool | Use When |
|---|---|
| `get_ticket` | Reading a ticket (required first step â€” returns digested recent history) |
| `get_session_log` | Reading one prior agent session's full progress log (debugging only) |
| `list_tickets` | Finding tickets by status, priority, assignee, tag |
| `update_ticket` | Changing metadata (title, priority, effort, tags, assignee, body) |
| `change_status` | Moving to a new status (requires comment for `Require Input` / `Ready`) |
| `add_comment` | Adding a comment to ticket history (persists to ticket) |
| `log_progress` | Recording progress updates (appears in history) |
| `create_ticket` | Creating a new ticket |
| `create_subtask` | Creating a child ticket linked to a parent |
| `finish_ticket` | Completing a ticket (atomic: sets link + adds comment + moves to Done) |
| `create_branch` | Create a feature branch for the ticket |
| `get_branch` | Check branch status, ahead/behind vs main |
| `delete_branch` | Delete ticket branch (refuses unmerged unless `force: true`) |
| `get_board_config` | Reading board configuration (statuses, tags) |

**Do not use:** chat comments, `log_progress` alone for findings, or direct file edits. Ticket findings must be persisted via `add_comment` or `update_ticket`.

