## APIs (Fallback Only)

The MCP tools are the primary interface. Use the REST API below **only if MCP tools fail to load** (never for convenience):

- `GET http://localhost:3067/api/tasks` â€” list tickets
- `PUT http://localhost:3067/api/tasks/:id` â€” update ticket (use `appendHistory` for comments)
- `POST http://localhost:3067/api/tasks` â€” create ticket
- `POST http://localhost:3067/api/tasks/:parentId/subtasks` â€” create subtask

